text: I see they killed the SW ride
That sellwood/tilikum is in it's place.
I would think that would be a far better ride - but still sucks to see absolutely zero love for biking on the left side of the river.
I miss the downtown/pearl/NW circuit, that was a fun one
The SW ride was very hilly compared to the other 4 rides - and commonly got rained out - so they never built up a base of people that were excited for it every year.
<@U02F8TTPU>: was the NW/pearl one in september?  I feel like the other 4 have been constant since I've been paying attention.
yowza, the last NW/Pearl Sunday Parkways was July 24, 2011
I would guess it was the most disruptive/expensive to host
The opening date for Tilikum Crossing is Sept 12th...  that's not much leeway (2 weeks) if they are late in opening the bridge.

attachments.title: Portland bicyclists, walkers will get to cross Tilikum Crossing early during one-day 'sneak peek'
attachments.text: Itching to cross Portland's new picturesque bridge over the Willamette River? You'll get your first chance on Aug. 9, 2015.
